  "prompt": "Is it possible to get into Andover without a sport?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to be admitted to Phillips Academy Andover without being an athlete. While sports can be a component of an application, Andover, like many elite preparatory schools, looks for well-rounded students who demonstrate strong academic abilities, leadership qualities, and diverse interests. Admissions committees at such schools consider a broad range of factors including academic achievements, extracurricular activities, personal essays, interviews, and recommendations. Engaging in arts, community service, clubs, or other activities can also strengthen an application. The key is to showcase your unique talents and how you would contribute to the school community.",
